OL,6,FThe chief medical officer for England,
OL,7,FProfessor Sir Chris Whitty, said:
OL,8,F"People who do not smoke but who are
OL,9,Fexposed to secondhand smoke can suffer
OL,10,Fsignificant harmful effects on their
OL,11,Fhealth, including an increased risk of
OL,12,Fasthma, poor birth outcomes, several
OL,13,Fcancers, stroke and heart disease.
